subject: Track and Field
lead_paragraph: Dalilah Muhammad led Cardozo High School of Queens to the girls’ team title with 78 points in the Public Schools Athletic League indoor championships at the New Balance Track and Field Center in Upper Manhattan. Muhammad won the high jump, finished second in the 55-meter hurdles and was third leg on Cardozo’s 4x800 winning relay (9:27.11). Midwood of Brooklyn captured the boys’ team crown with 51 points. Donald Williams paced Midwood with a victory in the 55-meter dash and ran second on Midwood’s winning 4x400 relay (3:28.60). Nadonna Rodrigues of Brooklyn’s Boys & Girls, who recently posted the fastest 400-meter time in the country at 52.83 seconds, took the 300 in 38.39 seconds and anchored her school’s winning 4x400 foursome (3:56.83).
